\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 ABSTRACT\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl300\slmult1\qj\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 The modeling of safety-critical systems requires rigorous safety analysis to prevent catastrophic failures. There is a historical gap between Goal-Oriented Requirements Engineering and detailed Safety Engineering techniques. The RESafety process was proposed to unify the iStar4Safety framework and the System-Theoretic Process Analysis (STPA) method; however, its manual execution demands high cognitive effort and time. This dissertation presents RESafety Tool as a web-based environment implemented with an Angular frontend integrated with Quarkus REST services. The current version operationalizes the RESafety workflow through authenticated project workspaces, an embedded iStar4Safety modeller, structured forms for STPA-oriented artifacts, and AI-assisted support for scope-definition activities. Rather than fully replacing the analyst, the tool adopts a human-in-the-loop strategy in which LLM outputs are proposed, reviewed, edited, and only then incorporated into the analysis. Preliminary results indicate that the implemented environment reduces operational effort, improves traceability among losses, hazards, constraints, and requirements, and lowers the practical barrier to adopting RESafety.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl300\slmult1\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Keywords:
\f1\b0  Requirements Engineering. Safety. STPA. iStar4Safety. Artificial Intelligence. RESafety Tool.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\partightenfactor0
